# Patch 0020 — Research branching + time-travel timeline (ROADMAP Phase 2.5;
# consumes ADR 0006 / patch 0019).
#
# BRANCHING: gZenWorkspaces.kavachaBranchSpace(snapshotId?) forks a space
# into a named alternative path — "Parent / branch". No snapshot id =
# branch NOW (snapshots first; dedup returning null falls back to the
# latest stored snapshot, which then IS the current state). The child space
# carries parentSpaceId / branchedFromSnapshotId / branchedAt on the space
# object (field-on-space pattern), inherits the parent's container, gets a
# COPY of the note (kavachaSetNote — same single-owner JSONFile as the
# notes panel), and rebuilds the snapshot's tabs.
#
# TIME-TRAVEL: kavachaOpenSpaceTimeline() lists the active space's
# snapshots (when / tab count / trigger) in a panel; "Restore as branch"
# forks that snapshot. Restore is deliberately NON-destructive — one
# mechanism (branching) serves both features and the present is never
# overwritten. Step-through replay is a follow-up. Both are palette
# commands ("Branch This Space", "Space Timeline") via the 0018 registry.
#
# Tab-rebuild mechanics, learned the hard way (all three bit during
# verification):
#   - addTrustedTab(url, {createLazyBrowser}) with the REAL url — blank
#     tabs get eaten by dedup and label the strip uselessly;
#   - the new tab lands in the ACTIVE space's container already, so
#     moveTabsToWorkspace early-continues before setting zen-workspace-id —
#     set the attribute explicitly or the tab is invisible to every filter;
#   - TabStateCache.update() takes per-datum fields ({history:{entries,
#     index}, scroll, formdata, image}), NOT getTabState's flat JSON —
#     the flat shape caches nothing and activation restores about:blank.
#   - the branch's strip element materializes async after the switch; wait
#     for workspaceElement(uuid).tabsContainer before parenting tabs.
# Pinned fidelity is a follow-up (everything restores unpinned); the branch
# keeps the starter New Tab a fresh space gets — harmless.
#
# Marionette-verified end to end: branch carries name/parent-pointer/tabs
# (lazy, correct labels)/note; activating a lazy branch tab restores the
# real page (url + title); timeline lists the parent's snapshots; Restore
# as branch creates a populated space. Applies on top of 0019.
